{"questionId":"14024","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>OAB is a sector of the circle with centre O and radius <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f4e4c153f29f32c4a40aff5f6977e07564e20460.png\"></p>\n<p>The angle AOB is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\theta \">\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span> radians, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 < \\theta&nbsp; < \\frac{\\pi }{2}\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>The point C lies on OA and OA is perpendicular to BC.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{OC}} = r\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta \"> <mrow> <mtext>OC</mtext> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mi>r</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{{{\\text{OC}}}}{r}\"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>OC</mtext> </mrow> </mrow> <mi>r</mi> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{OC}} = r\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta \"> <mrow> <mtext>OC</mtext> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mi>r</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span> &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG N0</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14024","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.S_4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that OC = r cos θ .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}